---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Laboratorio Laser - Publicaciones">
  <main class="main-content">
    <section class="banner-section">
      <img
        src="banner_publicaciones.png"
        alt="Publicaciones Banner"
        class="banner-img"
      />
    </section>

    <section class="publications-section">
      <h2 class="section-title">ARTÍCULOS ACADÉMICOS</h2>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-image">
          <!-- Placeholder image or the specific pig image if available. Using a generic placeholder for now as the asset was not provided, but ensuring <img> tag exists -->
          <img src="/publicacion_cerdos.png" alt="Cerdos Glässer" />
        </div>
        <div class="card-content">
          <h3 class="card-title">
            CONOCIMIENTOS GENÓMICOS SOBRE LA DIVERSIDAD, LA RESISTENCIA
            ANTIMICROBIANA Y LA VIRULENCIA DE GLAESSERELLA PARASUIS EN CERDOS
            ENFERMOS EN PERÚ
          </h3>
          <p class="card-text">
            Nuestro estudio publicado en Frontiers in Microbiology aporta nueva
            información clave sobre Glaesserella parasuis, la bacteria causante
            de la enfermedad de Glässer, a partir de aislamientos obtenidos en
            granjas porcinas del Perú. Mediante secuenciación completa del
            genoma, la investigación analiza la diversidad genética, los
            factores de virulencia y los perfiles de resistencia antimicrobiana,
            llenando un vacío importante de datos procedentes de Sudamérica.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .main-content {
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    font-family: sans-serif;
  }

  .banner-section {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .banner-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  .publications-section {
    max-width: 1000px; /* Same max-width as servicios for consistency */
    padding: 40px 20px;
    width: 100%;
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .section-title {
    text-align: center;
    color: #006400; /* Green color from image */
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 800;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 30px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .card-image {
    flex: 0 0 300px; /* Fixed width for image container */
  }

  .card-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px; /* Slight rounding if desired */
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .card-content {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .card-title {
    color: #4caf50; /* A slightly lighter green for the card title based on image? Or consistent dark green? Image looks like a lighter/vibrant green. Let's try #4CAF50 or keep #006400 matching branding. Image looks fairly matching. Let's use #4a8b4a or similar. Actually, let's stick to the branding #006400 or similar if needed. The image text looks like #4e9f3d or similar. I'll stick to a standard green. */
    color: #2e7d32;
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
    line-height: 1.4;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .card-text {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #333;
    text-align: justify;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .card {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    .card-image {
      flex: none;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 400px;
    }
  }
</style>
